race.description: Coolmore Spelling @ Mount White Razor Sharp (L)
race.comment: FIRE STAR (4) returned to form when a narrow second with the 59.5kg over 1300m at Newcastle. Comes back in trip and can tag the good tempo with the drop in weight. Fitted with a 1000m trial placing and will prove hard to hold out. WEEPING WOMAN (12) talented mare who deserves her chance at Listed level. Massive effort in the conditions when scoring again with the 61kg at Kembla Grange over this trip. Should measure up. BRAVE ONE (10) hit a career peak as fav when leading throughout for a dominant win over 1300m at Newcastle. Likely to race with cover from the draw and hard to stop in this vein of form. COAL CRUSHER (1) ran his rivals into the ground when a well deserved winner of the G2 The Hunter over 1300m at Newcastle. Since fitted with a trial win over 799m. Adept in all conditions and sure to be thereabouts. BARBER (3) capable on his day and the latest run had merit when closing fast to finish second in the LR Starlight over 1100m at Rosehill. Looking for the 1200m now.
